Actress Remi Oshodi aka Remi Surutu is grieving after losing her aged mum. The Nation was reliably informed that the actress’ mum passed away on Tuesday. Remi, who shares a striking resemblance with her mum, took to her Instagram page to announce the death of her mum.   Actress Laide Bakare acquires two new cars     I am a billionaire, Mercy Eke claims     Five renamed major landmarks in Lagos   “Maami is gone at age 101. Words fail me,” she wrote as a caption of her late mum’s picture shared on her Instagram page. Remi’s colleagues have been sending in their condolences. Some of the film practitioners that have sent in their condolences include Sikiratu Sindodo star, Tayo Odueke, Bimbo Thomas, Tayo Adeniyi, Tayo Sobola, Sola Kosoko, Ronke Odusanya, Adeniyi Johnson, Eniola Badmus, Ronke Ojo, Wunmi Toriola and Kemi Afolabi.